HEADWORD: Unyielded
<hw>Unyielded</hw>  <def>See <er>yielded</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
 ----- and the like.</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>To present participles which come from intransitive verbs, or are themselves employed as adjectives, to mark the absence of the activity, disposition, or condition implied by the participle;</def> as, --⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

